caption: We love, love love the food, atmosphere and people at Faros. We drove by today and were sad to see it closed even though online information says it's open. Will you be opening again?
Love this place. Amazing food and beautiful ambience
Great food. Great service.
Amazing greek salad
Excellent food and atmosphere. Recommend the saganaki and spanikopita.
Great quality food!
Good food friendly service
Great authentic Greek food

(Translated by Google) Very good place to eat and have a beer. Quiet and well attended and very beautiful. Good price  (Original) Sitio muy bueno para comer y tomar una cerveza. Tranquilo y bien atendido y muy bonito. Precio bueno

Every dish was well made and tasty. House red wise also paired just fine. Visited on a Sunday afternoon after a day in the park and was so pleased with the food and service. Had this spinach starter followed by lamb Youvetsi (Greek stew made with lamb and orzo). Baklava was lovely as dessert. Would go back again most definitely!
Lovely restaurant with attentive staff. The food is delicious. The lemon chicken dinner is excellent.
The service and the food very good highly suggested

A hidden gem in park slope. It’s easy to drive by this place and not take notice of it, but don’t make that mistake. Quiet atmosphere, friendly staff, generous portions and most importantly delicious.

Has to be one of the best spots in the area. Incredible food, generous portions and great service in a charming space. The Octopus was seasoned to perfection and flavorful (It wasn't the most tender, but I didn't mind the meaty texture) and the calamari and zucchini chips were amazing. The Marouli salad was simple but delicious.
It's a good restaurant. Very calm place and very good food
Nice and beautiful atmosphere

Really nice place on a rainy Tues night. Got there kind of late (9:15 - kitchen closes at 10) but they were very friendly and took good care of us. 2 of us split a fried calamari, an Athena salad, and a shrimp pasta w/ ouzo, along with a bottle of Greek red. All quite good (calamari and Garides Ouzu were excellent). $99+ tip.
Service took too long
Our go to place in the slope
Really happy to have a Greek restaurant of this caliber in my neighborhood. Rivals all of the best Greek restaurants in Queens. Truly authentic and delicious.
Excellent food
Very nice little Greek restaurant with a cozy and relaxing vibe. Food is good and the service is good too.
Excellent food

Beautiful food, incredible service, and elegant decor. Highly recommend the lamb shank with roasted potatoes or the fish stuffed with ricotta and spinach in some lemon sauce (or something). For dessert, get the Greek yogurt with honey and walnuts.
Cozy date spot with excellent Greek food. The tzatziki is wonderful!
Great place to visit! Loved it!
The atmosphere here is warm and inviting. The food is delicious, particularly the spanokopita. We primarily ordered appetizers to share across the table, and they made for an excellent meal.
Been going here since it opened, and it has improved a lot since. The service is excellent and the food is always delicious and generous. Wine selection is modest.
For the price, the food was good but not amazing. It wasn’t incredibly flavorful and portions were a bit small for certain things. But it had a nice atmosphere and service was good.
Quality, classic, Greek dishes in a cozy atmosphere. Expect a slightly higher price point, but only because it's worth some extra money. Recommend.

Great food, lovely service, and chill atmosphere.  There was basically no one in the restaurant when we got here on a Saturday, so we had the waitstaff's full attention, which was really nice considering the size of our group.  I ordered the Vegetarian Moussaka, which was delicious and quite filling.
Solid greek spot. Top notch saganaki.
Very tasty spinach pie!
Such great quality greek food
Authentic fresh and tasty Greek food at a reasonable price. It's truly a neighborhood gem.
Highly recommend if u in the mood for Classic Greek place. Tzatziki, Teremasalata, octopus all great at Faros.
Yummy

Good food, reasonably prices, nice location.  Service was slightly weird but still fine. Waiter seemed to be trying to wait us out until we ordered desserts.  He came over with a preprinted table tent advertising desserts.  He walked away again. Third time we told him teally, no dessert he picked up the table tent and took it away. Then he finally brought the check.
Authentic food, moderately priced, excellent service.
Wonderful food. Incredible hospitality.
Very pleasant sevice , food is very good ( I am not Greek so can't say if its authentic Greek food ). Definatelly coming back
Awful place, we were actually hinted to leave multiple times, and then we were specifically asked to leave by the restaurant workers. Will never go back!!!

Four of us ate an early dinner. We had a prix fixe menu, shared appetizers and each had our own entree. Very good food. Vegetarian and regular moussaka. Excellent service, tho I must admit we were about the only diners. Dessert was also very good. Rice pudding. Definitely recommend. Nice neighborhood place. Easily accessible tho bathrooms on the 2nd floor.

It was overpriced and the quality was not so good. The greek salad was particularly disappointing it was made since the morning and drowning in vinegar . The spinach pie was not made with traditional phylo but buttery sfoliata dough. Not really traditional greek cuisine and very disappointed with the price in the end. I really miss Greece and this place didn't make me feel like home.
Excellent food and service.
Great atmosphere I’ve ever seen , delicious food made by Greek chef , lovely place  for all kind of situation
Service is so terrible and price is too expansive for that quality of food.
Seafood is really fresh and delicious I highly recommend octopus and calamari
Amazing place, with high class service and the best Greek food i have ever had in any country.
The restaurant was OK. Not the best Greek i've had. I would have given 3.5 stars if it were an option. Staff was OK, not super attentive. Food OK, nothing outstanding. Overall it was just OK.
hi this is Miriam from the agency in  Brklyn :) nice to meet you and looking forward coming over to see the place :)
Food is excellent
Good place

When I first walked in, I felt like I was stepping into a taverna in Greece.  Service is gracious and attentive.  The grilled octopus is incredibly tender.  The bronzino fresh and tasty.  Can't wait to try the other Greek specialties..
Great service, waiters are super helpful. Food is delicious.
A lovely restaurant with fresh and yummy food.  The service is charming and you'll have a wonderful meal.
Annette is in charge and the results are superb. Home, cozy atmosphere. Warm friendly service, excellent blending of tastes, fresh foods and "Annette".
Good food, great little place and very good service, reasonable prices
Very nice place , very friendly staff, good food

This is  the best restaurants around the Park slope Great food and an excellent service,  i suggest to everyone this restaurant. It has wonderful outdoor terrace and quality environment. Servers serve you quick and smiley. I will always go to this restaurant.
Great food
had a great meal here
Had a brunch there was really good

Came here early afternoon for brunch two couples and one kid. Very friendly people, Nice service, good food, good price, nice romantic/relaxing atmosphere and very nice with the kid. What more can you ask for

Great find!  Food was amazing, had octopus (i didn't eat it but hubby found it one of the best he's had), greek salad and tatziki.  Had the pork loin for a main and the entire dish had wonderful flavor!  Hubby had the branzino special and absolutely raved about it.  Price was mid range but well worth it.  Beautiful ambiance, great for dinner, and the staff was very friendly and helpful.  Cannot wait to come back.
This is one of the best greek places I've ever been to. The service is awesome and the food is amazing. They have a lemon chicken dish that was spectacular.
Fresh food and quality ingredients. We came for brunch and seemed to get a lot for the money.  The back patio was great and the waiters were friendly.
Cheap attempt of a restaurant.
Very good Greek food. Light, well seasoned tasty food. Good service too.
true Greek food, served fast, very impressed.
Tastey and there's always room at the bar.

My husband and I have had many truly delicious meals here. The decor is lovely, the menu extensive (and fabulous) and unlike so many Park Slope eateries it caters to adults - no kiddie menu, no cartoons on screens and no strollers. Just wonderful food, excellent service and a warm, welcoming environment.
Amazing staff, great food, wonderful drinks. I love the Sunday brunch and the mimosa taste so good. If you like feta cheese this is the place to go, very good Greek food.
I love this restaurant

I had a surprisingly pleasant time here.  My party was seated on the back deck.  The place was packed to the gills at 6:30.  The food ranges from good to great.  The appetizer platter we got for the table was superb.  Everybody cleaned their plates.  Beer was terrible and service was extremely slow.   Despite those last two points I will return next time I am in the mood for some upscale Greek.

My name is Josue Aguilar and this restaurant is not sanitary. The cooks cook with bare hands. They serve the food and make the plates with their bare hands. The kitchen is in the basement. Their's a fish platter that's served split down the middle and nobody uses gloves to open the fish. I was told to wear gloves when inspection comes. There's flour that has been contaminated with food that's left their over night-so its at room temperature. You can believe what you want. Its your health not mine.
Fabulous quick delivery. Menu covers the basics of Greek food. Solid pasticcio and large salads, clearly meant to be shared.
